Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.10,0:00:11.28,统计en,,0,0,0,,By now, thanks to our lesson on circuit analysis and previous Crash Course Physics episodes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.10,0:00:11.28,统计ch,,0,0,0,,根据之前的电路分析与我们的课程学习
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:13.66,统计en,,0,0,0,,you know your way around a basic DC circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:13.66,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你知道我们马上就要来研究直流电路了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.92,0:00:15.92,统计en,,0,0,0,,You've learned how to simplify circuits with resistors
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.92,0:00:18.43,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你已经学会如何简化串联和并联的简单电阻电路了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.92,0:00:18.43,统计en,,0,0,0,,connected in series and parallel with a single battery source,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.43,0:00:18.98,统计en,,0,0,0,,which is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.43,0:00:18.98,统计ch,,0,0,0,,很厉害
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.12,0:00:21.77,统计en,,0,0,0,,But a lot of the real-world circuits that you encounter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.12,0:00:22.75,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但我们实际生活中的电路
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:22.75,统计en,,0,0,0,,and will have to describe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:24.26,统计en,,0,0,0,,are much more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:24.26,统计ch,,0,0,0,,要复杂的多 我们稍后会讲
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.46,0:00:26.54,统计en,,0,0,0,,For example, what happens when there are multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.54,0:00:28.30,统计en,,0,0,0,,batteries, connected in parallel?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.46,0:00:28.30,统计ch,,0,0,0,,例如 多个电池并联是什么情况？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.42,0:00:30.99,统计en,,0,0,0,,And what happens when we add capacitors into the mix,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.42,0:00:32.77,统计ch,,0,0,0,,当我们在电阻电路中加入电容时应该怎么分析
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.99,0:00:32.77,统计en,,0,0,0,,with resistors in our DC circuits?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.77,0:00:35.64,统计en,,0,0,0,,On this, our last go-round inside a DC circuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.77,0:00:35.64,统计ch,,0,0,0,,在电学部分的最后一次课中
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:38.53,统计en,,0,0,0,,we'll encounter junctions, loops, and capacitors!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:38.53,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们来讲讲电容 节点以及环路
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.53,0:00:49.82,统计ch,,0,0,0,,翻译 {\c&HA7EC09&}天下第②帅 {\c\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.26,0:00:53.92,统计en,,0,0,0,,Circuits aren't always just a battery powering a set of resistors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.26,0:00:53.92,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电路并不仅有电源和电阻
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.00,0:00:57.31,统计en,,0,0,0,,The design of a circuit depends on the needs of the system it operates,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.00,0:00:57.31,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电路的设计来自系统运行的需求
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.31,0:01:00.53,统计en,,0,0,0,,and we need tools to take any configuration into account.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.31,0:01:00.53,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们需要一个可以研究任何电路的工具
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.56,0:01:04.04,批注,,0,0,0,, Gustav Kirchhoff\N古斯塔夫 基尔霍夫
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.56,0:01:04.04,统计en,,0,0,0,,In the mid 19th century, a German physicist named Gustav Kirchhoff
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.56,0:01:04.04,统计ch,,0,0,0,,19世纪中期 德国的物理学家Gustav Kirchhoff
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.40,0:01:07.50,统计en,,0,0,0,,expanded on the principles of Ohm's law to improve our ability
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.40,0:01:07.50,统计ch,,0,0,0,,拓展了欧姆定律
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.50,0:01:11.00,统计en,,0,0,0,,to calculate current and voltage in complex electrical circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.50,0:01:11.00,统计ch,,0,0,0,,让我们可以计算复杂电路中的电流与电压
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:15.61,统计en,,0,0,0,,Kirchhoff took laws we already knew: the conservation of charge and of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:15.61,统计ch,,0,0,0,,他根据我们已知的电荷和能量守恒的关系
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.87,0:01:18.46,统计en,,0,0,0,,and established two rules for circuit analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.87,0:01:18.46,统计ch,,0,0,0,,提出了电路分析的两条准则
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.46,0:01:22.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,is something we've actually already discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.51,0:01:20.62,统计en,,0,0,0,,The first rule, which deals with conservation of charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.51,0:01:22.51,统计ch,,0,0,0,,第一条准则与我们已经讨论过的电荷守恒有关
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.70,0:01:30.23,批注,,0,0,0,,也就是基尔霍夫电流定律 \N简记为KCL
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.70,0:01:24.35,统计en,,0,0,0,,It's known as Kirchhoff's Junction Rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.70,0:01:24.35,统计ch,,0,0,0,,叫做节点电流定律
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.59,0:01:27.52,统计en,,0,0,0,,and it states that the sum of all currents entering into a junction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.59,0:01:27.52,统计ch,,0,0,0,,流入某节点的电流的总和
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.71,0:01:30.23,统计en,,0,0,0,,is equal to the sum of all currents leaving the junction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.71,0:01:30.23,统计ch,,0,0,0,,等于流出该节点的电流总和
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.35,0:01:33.13,统计en,,0,0,0,,Like I've been saying: What goes in must come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.35,0:01:33.13,统计ch,,0,0,0,,就像我一直说的：有进必有出
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.31,0:01:35.31,统计en,,0,0,0,,The second rule, based on the conservation of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.31,0:01:35.31,统计ch,,0,0,0,,第二个准则基于能量守恒
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.31,0:01:38.21,统计en,,0,0,0,,is a little harder to grasp, but trust me, it works!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.31,0:01:38.21,统计ch,,0,0,0,,虽然有点难懂 但相信我 这是真的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.21,0:01:44.00,批注,,0,0,0,,也就是基尔霍夫电压定律\N简记为KVL
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.21,0:01:39.71,统计en,,0,0,0,,It's Kirchhoff's Loop Rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.21,0:01:39.71,统计ch,,0,0,0,,称为回路电压定律
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.71,0:01:44.00,统计en,,0,0,0,,and it says that the sum of all changes in potential around a loop equals zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.71,0:01:44.00,统计ch,,0,0,0,,说的是闭合回路中所有元件两端电动势的变化之和等于零
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.09,0:01:46.00,统计en,,0,0,0,,So, why would you need to know that's a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.09,0:01:46.00,统计ch,,0,0,0,,知道这个准则能怎么样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:48.17,统计en,,0,0,0,,Well, remember, batteries supply potential,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:48.17,统计ch,,0,0,0,,想想 电源提供电动势
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.17,0:01:50.49,统计en,,0,0,0,,and then that potential, also called voltage,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.17,0:01:50.49,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电动势又叫做电压
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.83,0:01:52.18,统计en,,0,0,0,,drops across resistors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.83,0:01:52.18,统计ch,,0,0,0,,经过电阻时会降低
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.18,0:01:54.14,统计en,,0,0,0,,It's kind of like a ride on a roller coaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.18,0:01:54.14,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这有点像乘坐过山车
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.14,0:01:56.64,统计en,,0,0,0,,You may climb up steep slopes and fly around the track,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.14,0:01:56.64,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你可以沿着轨道飞来飞去
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.64,0:02:00.08,统计en,,0,0,0,,doing loop-da-loops to your heart's content and your stomach's discontent
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.64,0:02:00.08,统计ch,,0,0,0,,刺激你的心脏 折磨你的胃
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.08,0:02:02.81,统计en,,0,0,0,,but you always start and end in the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.08,0:02:02.81,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但你总会在同一个地方停下
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.84,0:02:05.85,统计en,,0,0,0,,Likewise, in a circuit, every battery is like a climb in height, gaining potential,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.84,0:02:05.85,统计ch,,0,0,0,,在电路中 电源就像是上升段 提高电动势
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:08.78,统计en,,0,0,0,,and each resistor is a drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:08.78,统计ch,,0,0,0,,而每个电阻是下降段 消耗电动势
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:10.68,统计en,,0,0,0,,But no matter which way you go in the circuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:10.68,统计ch,,0,0,0,,无论你在电路中走哪条路
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:12.46,统计en,,0,0,0,,you'll always end up where you started.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:12.46,统计ch,,0,0,0,,都要回到起始的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:14.33,统计en,,0,0,0,,So let's put these rules to the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:14.33,统计ch,,0,0,0,,所以我们来验证这两个规则吧
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:17.52,统计en,,0,0,0,,Here's a circuit that wouldn't be easy to solve with only Ohm's law.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:17.52,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这个电路只用欧姆定律不太好做
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.71,0:02:20.03,统计en,,0,0,0,,It has two batteries and four resistors,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.71,0:02:20.03,统计ch,,0,0,0,,它包含两处电源和四个电阻
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:22.65,统计en,,0,0,0,,with a combination of series and parallel connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:22.65,统计ch,,0,0,0,,既有串联也有并联
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.72,0:02:25.90,统计en,,0,0,0,,You can simplify the two resistors in series down to one,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.72,0:02:25.90,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你可以先把这俩电阻合成一个
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:28.21,统计en,,0,0,0,,but after that, how do you tackle the rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:28.21,统计ch,,0,0,0,,然后就做不下去了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.38,0:02:30.32,统计en,,0,0,0,,If you want to find the current through each branch,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.38,0:02:30.32,统计ch,,0,0,0,,如果你想求出每个支路的电路
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.32,0:02:32.28,统计en,,0,0,0,,and the voltage drop across each resistor,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.32,0:02:32.28,统计ch,,0,0,0,,以及每个电阻两端的电压
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.52,0:02:33.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,you're gonna need Gustav's help!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.52,0:02:33.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你就需要基尔霍夫的帮助
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.03,0:02:37.34,统计en,,0,0,0,,The first step of using the junction rule is to label all the junctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.03,0:02:37.34,统计ch,,0,0,0,,使用KCL前你需要找到所以的节点
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.37,批注,,0,0,0,,每个（串联）元件就是一条支路\N同一条支路上电流处处相等
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.37,统计en,,0,0,0,,Each junction is a point on a wire that's connected to two or more circuit elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.37,统计ch,,0,0,0,,节点是超过一条支路的交点
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:43.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,Then, you label all the different currents in the diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:43.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,然后标出不同支路的电流值
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:45.66,统计en,,0,0,0,,There are only three different wire branches,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:45.66,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这个电路只有三个分支
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.66,0:02:47.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,so there are three different currents in the circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.66,0:02:47.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因此要标出三个电流
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.12,0:02:52.46,统计en,,0,0,0,,Kirchhoff's junction rule tells us that everything entering junction “a” must leave it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.12,0:02:52.46,统计ch,,0,0,0,,KCL告诉我们 流入节点a的一切电流都会流出
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:57.15,统计en,,0,0,0,,Mathematically, this means that I2 is equal to the sum of I1 and I3,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:57.15,统计ch,,0,0,0,,写出数学表达式就是 I2 = I1 + I3
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:02:59.91,统计en,,0,0,0,,since it's I2 that splits off into two branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:02:59.91,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为 I1 和 I3 是 I2 的两个分支
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.91,0:03:02.91,统计en,,0,0,0,,Notice, by the way, that we've assigned the current directions the way we have,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.91,0:03:02.91,统计ch,,0,0,0,,注意我们是怎么定义电流方向的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:05.74,统计en,,0,0,0,,because they make sense with the orientation of the batteries,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:08.24,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们定义 电源内部的电流方向是从负到正
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.74,0:03:08.24,统计en,,0,0,0,,going from the negative to positive terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:10.16,统计en,,0,0,0,,But no matter which way you orient them, in your equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:10.16,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但无论你怎么定义方向
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:13.41,统计en,,0,0,0,,all the values will work out the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:13.41,统计ch,,0,0,0,,整体的相对关系的保持不变的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:15.68,统计en,,0,0,0,,If you've correctly chosen the direction of current,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:15.68,统计ch,,0,0,0,,方向选择正确后
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:18.31,统计en,,0,0,0,,then their values will come out positive, like current should.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:18.31,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电流值就是正的 这是显然的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.31,0:03:19.98,统计en,,0,0,0,,But if you've chosen the wrong direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.31,0:03:19.98,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但如果方向反了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.98,0:03:21.61,统计en,,0,0,0,,then the value will end up being negative!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.98,0:03:21.61,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电流值就是负的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.61,0:03:22.97,统计en,,0,0,0,,OK, back to the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.61,0:03:22.97,统计ch,,0,0,0,,好了 继续做题
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.48,统计en,,0,0,0,,Let's call the equation with the current values "equation one"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.48,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们先把这个电流关系式叫做”方程1“
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:27.19,统计en,,0,0,0,,and return to it later, when we need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:27.19,统计ch,,0,0,0,,后面会用到它
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.19,0:03:29.59,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now it's time to try out Kirchhoff's Loop Rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.19,0:03:29.59,统计ch,,0,0,0,,现在来用KVL了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.59,0:03:36.69,批注,,0,0,0,,回路是闭合的支路\N这个电路可以画3个回路
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.59,0:03:31.69,统计en,,0,0,0,,You can draw a loop around any part of the circuit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.59,0:03:31.69,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你可以任意画一个回路
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:34.99,统计en,,0,0,0,,where you can imagine a charged particle moving around the circuit in a circle,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:34.99,统计ch,,0,0,0,,然后想象电荷沿着回路绕圈
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.32,0:03:36.69,统计en,,0,0,0,,ending back where it started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.32,0:03:36.69,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但每次都会回到起点
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:39.86,统计en,,0,0,0,,To put it simply, wherever there's a loop,we can use the loop rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:39.86,统计ch,,0,0,0,,简而言之 只要有回路我们就可以用KVL
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.93,0:03:41.95,统计en,,0,0,0,,We've got one loop in the top half of the circuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.93,0:03:41.95,统计ch,,0,0,0,,上半圈有一个回路
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.95,0:03:43.52,统计en,,0,0,0,,and a second loop in the bottom half,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.95,0:03:43.52,统计ch,,0,0,0,,下半圈也有一个
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:45.76,统计en,,0,0,0,,and there's actually a third loop here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:45.76,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这个也是回路
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:47.90,统计en,,0,0,0,,It's the entire outside of the circuit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:47.90,统计ch,,0,0,0,,是整个电路的外圈
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:48.76,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now you've got your loops,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:48.76,统计ch,,0,0,0,,找到回路后
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:51.71,统计en,,0,0,0,,and you're going to use them to solve the three unknown current values.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:51.71,统计ch,,0,0,0,,就可以算出未知的三个电流值了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.98,0:03:53.52,统计en,,0,0,0,,Let's begin with loop number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.98,0:03:53.52,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们从回路1开始
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:55.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,In this loop, you have one 20 Volt battery
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:55.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这个回路中 有一个20V的电源
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.06,0:03:59.08,统计en,,0,0,0,,and two resistors, a 5 Ohm and a 40 Ohm one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.06,0:03:59.08,统计ch,,0,0,0,,还有两个电阻 分别是5Ω和40Ω
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.08,0:04:01.10,统计en,,0,0,0,,You know that there's a voltage gain across the battery
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.08,0:04:01.10,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们知道电源可以提高电压
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.10,0:04:04.53,统计en,,0,0,0,,and a voltage drop across both resistor 2 and resistor 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.10,0:04:04.53,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电阻1和电阻2消耗电压
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.62,0:04:07.05,统计en,,0,0,0,,The voltage gain across the battery is 20 Volts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.62,0:04:07.05,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电源升高的电压是20V
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.37,0:04:10.08,统计en,,0,0,0,,but you don't know the voltage drops across the resistors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.37,0:04:10.08,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但你不知道两个电阻消耗的电压
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.12,0:04:13.90,统计en,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Ohm's law, you can substitute the voltage drop across each resistor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.12,0:04:13.90,统计ch,,0,0,0,,根据欧姆定律 我们可以把电阻消耗的电压
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.22,0:04:16.02,统计en,,0,0,0,,with the current times the resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.22,0:04:16.02,统计ch,,0,0,0,,表示成电流乘上电阻值
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:19.54,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now you've got two unknowns in this equation, which we'll call "equation two."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:19.54,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这个式子中有两个未知量 我们叫做“方程2”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.54,0:04:21.06,统计en,,0,0,0,,Let's set that aside as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.54,0:04:21.06,统计ch,,0,0,0,,写出来放在一边
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:22.83,统计en,,0,0,0,,Next, let's look at loop two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:22.83,统计ch,,0,0,0,,接下来看回路2
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.83,0:04:25.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,In this loop, you've got two batteries and three resistors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.83,0:04:25.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,在这个回路中有两个电源和三个电阻
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.93,0:04:27.36,统计en,,0,0,0,,If you follow the direction of the loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.93,0:04:27.36,统计ch,,0,0,0,,如果你顺着电流方向看
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:29.66,统计en,,0,0,0,,you see that both batteries add voltage,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:29.66,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你会发现两个电源都是提供正压的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.93,0:04:33.39,统计en,,0,0,0,,because the loop direction goes from their negative end through to the positive end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.93,0:04:33.39,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为它们内部的电流都是从负到正
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:36.35,统计en,,0,0,0,,Additionally, all the resistors will subtract voltage,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:36.35,统计ch,,0,0,0,,而且所有的电阻都消耗电压
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:38.80,统计en,,0,0,0,,because the loop goes in the same direction as the current.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:38.80,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为环路的方向与电流同向
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.99,0:04:41.48,统计en,,0,0,0,,So it's important to draw your current directions first,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.99,0:04:41.48,统计ch,,0,0,0,,所以最重要的是确定电流的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:42.72,统计en,,0,0,0,,in order to make this clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:42.72,统计ch,,0,0,0,,后面才不会乱套
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.76,0:04:45.24,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now, you want to do the same thing you did for the first loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.76,0:04:45.24,统计ch,,0,0,0,,现在你想重复回路1的操作
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:48.12,批注,,0,0,0,,即电压的代数和等于零
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:48.12,统计en,,0,0,0,,which is to sum up all the changes in voltage to 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:48.12,统计ch,,0,0,0,,让所有电压的变化量为0
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:51.29,统计en,,0,0,0,,And then you just substitute Ohm's law in for every resistor's voltage,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:51.29,统计ch,,0,0,0,,然后根据欧姆定律
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:53.37,统计en,,0,0,0,,to get terms of current and resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:53.37,统计ch,,0,0,0,,用电流与电阻的积来替换电压
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:04:56.25,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now you have this third equation, which we'll call "equation three."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:04:56.25,统计ch,,0,0,0,,现在我们有了“方程3”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:04:58.84,统计en,,0,0,0,,While you could go on and create an equation for the third loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:04:58.84,统计ch,,0,0,0,,虽然你可以继续计算环路3
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:00.32,统计en,,0,0,0,,you actually don't need to,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:00.32,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但这是多余的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.46,0:05:02.83,统计en,,0,0,0,,because the junction rule gives you an equation to use here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.46,0:05:02.83,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为KCL已经提供了“方程1”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:05.69,统计en,,0,0,0,,So at this point, you have the three equations\Nyou need to solve everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:05.69,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这个节点的三个未知数已经有了三个独立方程
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.79,0:05:07.69,统计en,,0,0,0,,So let's first revisit equation one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.79,0:05:11.64,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们将方程2的 I1 和方程3的 I3 带入方程1
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.69,0:05:11.64,统计en,,0,0,0,,and replace I1 and I3 with equations two and three.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:14.27,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now you have an equation entirely in terms of I2,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:14.27,统计ch,,0,0,0,,现在你有了一个只含 I2 的方程
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:17.68,统计en,,0,0,0,,which you can solve to find that I2 is equal to 1 Ampere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:17.68,统计ch,,0,0,0,,解得 I2 = 1A
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.68,0:05:18.96,统计en,,0,0,0,,Once you have this value,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.68,0:05:18.96,统计ch,,0,0,0,,解出 I2 的值后
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.15,0:05:20.91,统计en,,0,0,0,,you can easily solve equations two and three
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.15,0:05:20.91,统计ch,,0,0,0,,带入到方程2和3中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:23.04,统计en,,0,0,0,,by substituting in the new I2 solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:23.04,统计ch,,0,0,0,,就可以很容易解出 I1 和 I3
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:24.18,统计en,,0,0,0,,And there you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:24.18,统计ch,,0,0,0,,然后就解完了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.18,0:05:27.21,统计en,,0,0,0,,If you wanted to know any of the voltage drops across the resistors,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.18,0:05:27.21,统计ch,,0,0,0,,如果要求任意电阻的压降
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.61,0:05:30.38,统计en,,0,0,0,,all you'd have to do is multiply the resistance in question
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.61,0:05:30.38,统计ch,,0,0,0,,只需要用相应电阻的阻值
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.65,0:05:32.77,统计en,,0,0,0,,by the current passing through that resistor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.65,0:05:32.77,统计ch,,0,0,0,,乘上通过该电阻的电流
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.84,0:05:35.60,统计en,,0,0,0,,For instance, the voltage drop across resistor 2
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.84,0:05:41.63,统计ch,,0,0,0,,例如，电阻2两端的压降就是5Ω的电阻乘上1A的电流
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:37.74,统计en,,0,0,0,,would be the resistance, 5 Ohms,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.04,0:05:41.63,统计en,,0,0,0,,multiplied by the current passing through that resistor, which is 1 Ampere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:43.99,统计en,,0,0,0,,That's a total voltage drop of 5 Volts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:43.99,统计ch,,0,0,0,,总压降就是5V
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:46.11,统计en,,0,0,0,,And the drop across resistor 1 in the same loop
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:51.88,统计ch,,0,0,0,,同回路中的电阻1的压降为40Ω的电阻乘上0.375A的电流
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.36,0:05:48.12,统计en,,0,0,0,,would be the resistance, 40 Ohms,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.49,0:05:51.88,统计en,,0,0,0,,times the current through the resistor, which is 0.375 Amperes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:54.56,统计en,,0,0,0,,That comes out to a voltage drop of 15 Volts,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:54.56,统计ch,,0,0,0,,出现了15V的压降
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:55.56,统计en,,0,0,0,,which makes sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:55.56,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这就对了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:05:57.47,统计en,,0,0,0,,because then the sum of each drop in the loop
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:05:57.47,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为环路的电压变化
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.68,0:05:59.86,统计en,,0,0,0,,is equal to the voltage supplied by the battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.68,0:05:59.86,统计ch,,0,0,0,,等于电源提供的电压
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:03.95,统计en,,0,0,0,,And those are Kirchhoff's Laws – the Junction Rule for current and the Loop Rule for voltage,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:03.95,统计ch,,0,0,0,,上面讲的就是KCL和KVL的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:06.35,统计en,,0,0,0,,with a little Ohm's law utilization as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:06.35,统计ch,,0,0,0,,也用上了一点欧姆定律
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:09.22,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now it's time to reintroduce our old friend the capacitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:09.22,统计ch,,0,0,0,,现在来重新认识我们的老朋友 电容器
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:13.50,统计en,,0,0,0,,In a DC circuit, a capacitor is useful for storing charge temporarily,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:15.07,统计ch,,0,0,0,,在直流电路中 电容器用于充放电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.50,0:06:15.07,统计en,,0,0,0,,then releasing it again later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.07,0:06:18.25,统计en,,0,0,0,,But so far we've been dealing with circuits that have a constant flow of charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.07,0:06:18.25,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但目前我们碰到的都是电荷恒定
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.60,0:06:20.22,统计en,,0,0,0,,or those that have reached steady state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.60,0:06:20.22,统计ch,,0,0,0,,或者到达稳态的电路
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:23.08,统计en,,0,0,0,,With capacitors, we deal with transient conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:23.08,统计ch,,0,0,0,,有了电容后 我们可以处理瞬态条件
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:25.31,统计en,,0,0,0,,or circuit responses that change with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:25.31,统计ch,,0,0,0,,或者时变的电路响应
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.31,0:06:28.80,统计en,,0,0,0,,From our earlier lessons, you know that the amount of charge stored in a capacitor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.31,0:06:28.80,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们已经知道 存储在电容器中的电荷量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:32.83,统计en,,0,0,0,,is equal to the voltage across the capacitor times its capacitance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:32.83,统计ch,,0,0,0,,等于电容器两端的电压乘上电容量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:36.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,And you can store this charge by connecting a capacitor in series with a battery,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:36.51,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你可以把电容与电源串联
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.81,0:06:39.31,统计en,,0,0,0,,letting current flow from the battery into the capacitor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.81,0:06:39.31,统计ch,,0,0,0,,使电流从电源流入电容
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.60,0:06:42.24,统计en,,0,0,0,,until the capacitor's voltage is equal to the battery's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.60,0:06:42.24,统计ch,,0,0,0,,直到电容的电压等于电源的电压 从而储存电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:45.28,统计en,,0,0,0,,But what happens when you connect multiple capacitors together,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:45.28,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但如果多个电容组合在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:47.92,统计en,,0,0,0,,like we do with resistors, in series and in parallel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:47.92,统计ch,,0,0,0,,像电阻串联或并联时 会发生什么
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.00,0:06:50.78,统计en,,0,0,0,,Well, if you have several capacitors connected in parallel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.00,0:06:53.31,统计ch,,0,0,0,,并联的电容使电路的整体电容增加
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:53.31,统计en,,0,0,0,,the overall capacitance of the circuit increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:54.72,统计en,,0,0,0,,In this circuit diagram,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:58.10,统计ch,,0,0,0,,在这个电路中 三个电容器与同一个电源相接
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:58.10,统计en,,0,0,0,,we have three capacitors\Nconnected in parallel with a single battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:06:59.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,Current will flow into the capacitors,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:06:59.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电荷会流入每个电容
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:02.95,统计en,,0,0,0,,and will stop when each capacitor holds the maximum amount of charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:02.95,统计ch,,0,0,0,,分别充满后停止
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:06.42,统计en,,0,0,0,,So, how can you describe the equivalent capacitance\Nof a circuit like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:06.42,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这种情况怎么能描述等效电容呢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.42,0:07:09.29,统计en,,0,0,0,,Easy: the total amount of charge is the sum of the charges
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.42,0:07:11.13,统计ch,,0,0,0,,很简单 总电荷量是每个电容的电荷之和
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.29,0:07:11.13,统计en,,0,0,0,,held by each individual capacitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:16.92,统计en,,0,0,0,,is equal to the capacitance times the voltage across each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:16.92,统计ch,,0,0,0,,而你知道每个电容的电荷等于电压乘上电容
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.21,0:07:13.52,统计en,,0,0,0,,And you know that the charge held by each capacitor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.05,0:07:19.82,统计en,,0,0,0,,And since every point of a conductor has the same potential,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.05,0:07:19.82,统计ch,,0,0,0,,导体每个点的电动势相等
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.06,0:07:21.63,批注,,0,0,0,,而所有的导体串联在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.06,0:07:21.63,统计en,,0,0,0,,and all the conductors are connected,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.93,0:07:24.77,统计en,,0,0,0,,all devices connected in parallel will have the same voltage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.93,0:07:24.77,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因此所有并联的元件电压相等
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.91,0:07:26.84,统计en,,0,0,0,,So, you can simplify the charge equation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.91,0:07:26.84,统计ch,,0,0,0,,所以 电荷方程可以化简
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:29.66,统计en,,0,0,0,,to say that the equivalent capacitance of the circuit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:32.27,统计ch,,0,0,0,,然后得到 并联电路的等效电容等于每个电容之和
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:32.27,统计en,,0,0,0,,is equal to the sum of all the individual capacitances.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:35.75,批注,,0,0,0,,却和电阻的串联类似
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:35.75,统计en,,0,0,0,,Note that this is the not the same as the parallel equation for resistors!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:35.75,统计ch,,0,0,0,,请注意 这与电阻的并联方程不同
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.75,0:07:37.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,Capacitance is unique in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.75,0:07:37.51,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电容和电阻还是有区别的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.51,0:07:41.07,统计en,,0,0,0,,In fact, the convention is also reversed for capacitors connected in series,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.51,0:07:41.07,统计en,,0,0,0,,事实上 电容与电阻的串联情况也是相反的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:43.45,统计en,,0,0,0,,which will have a lower overall capacitance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:43.45,统计ch,,0,0,0,,串联电容的等效值更低
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.58,0:07:48.38,统计en,,0,0,0,,For example, if you have a circuit with three capacitors connected in series with a single battery,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.58,0:07:48.38,统计ch,,0,0,0,,如果电路中有三个电容器与电源串联
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.89,0:07:54.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,then the current still stops flowing when the total voltage across the capacitors equals that of the battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.89,0:07:54.51,统计ch,,0,0,0,,当三个电容的总电压等于电源电压时 充电停止
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.51,0:07:57.02,统计en,,0,0,0,,The charge contained by each capacitor is the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.51,0:07:57.02,统计ch,,0,0,0,,每个电容器所含的电荷量相等
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.36,0:07:59.60,统计en,,0,0,0,,because current can't flow through the capacitors,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.36,0:07:59.60,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为电流不能流过电容
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.96,0:08:01.48,统计en,,0,0,0,,only on either side of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.96,0:08:01.48,统计ch,,0,0,0,,只能在电容的某一侧流动
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.56,0:08:04.35,统计en,,0,0,0,,So if one plate of the first capacitor has a positive charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.56,0:08:04.35,统计ch,,0,0,0,,如果第一个电容的左极板带有正电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.78,0:08:08.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,then the other plate in that first capacitor has an equal and opposite negative charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.78,0:08:08.87,统计ch,,0,0,0,,那么右极板会带有等量的负电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.94,0:08:10.94,统计en,,0,0,0,,This leads the plate of the next capacitor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.94,0:08:13.07,统计ch,,0,0,0,,这导致第二个电容的左极板带有等量的正电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.94,0:08:13.07,统计en,,0,0,0,,to have an equal and opposite positive charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.16,0:08:14.60,统计en,,0,0,0,,since the amount of charge in the plates,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.16,0:08:17.30,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为极板的电荷量以及导线并没有变
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.60,0:08:17.30,统计en,,0,0,0,,and the wire that connects them, hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:20.69,统计en,,0,0,0,,But the nearby charged plate redistributes the charge to compensate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:20.69,统计ch,,0,0,0,,但相邻的极板会重新分配电荷进行补偿
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.69,0:08:22.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,This effect carries all the way through,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.69,0:08:28.51,统计ch,,0,0,0,,一直传递到最后一个电容的右极板 直到它充满与第一个电容左极板等量的负电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.51,0:08:25.87,统计en,,0,0,0,,until the last plate of the third capacitor has a negative charge
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.87,0:08:28.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,equal and opposite to the first capacitor's positive plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.62,0:08:31.20,统计en,,0,0,0,,So you can picture the entire set of capacitors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.62,0:08:31.20,统计ch,,0,0,0,,所以可以将串联的所有电容
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.45,0:08:33.29,统计en,,0,0,0,,as one big equivalent capacitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.45,0:08:33.29,统计ch,,0,0,0,,看成一个等效电容
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.48,0:08:36.33,统计en,,0,0,0,,For devices in series, the voltage drops across each element
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.48,0:08:36.33,统计ch,,0,0,0,,对于串联的元件
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:38.51,统计en,,0,0,0,,equal the voltage provided by the battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:38.51,统计ch,,0,0,0,,压降之和等于电池提供的电压
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.51,0:08:40.76,统计en,,0,0,0,,So to find the equivalent capacitance in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.51,0:08:40.76,统计ch,,0,0,0,,为了找到串联电容的等效电容值
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:45.20,统计en,,0,0,0,,just substitute in the charge equation (voltage-times-capacitance)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:47.36,统计ch,,0,0,0,,只需要把电压方程中的每个电压替换为电荷量除以对应电容
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.20,0:08:47.36,统计en,,0,0,0,,for each voltage across the capacitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:50.03,统计en,,0,0,0,,The charge contained by each capacitor is still the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:50.03,统计ch,,0,0,0,,每个电容器所含的电荷量相等
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:53.08,统计en,,0,0,0,,since the charge on each positive and negative plate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:54.44,统计ch,,0,0,0,,因为每个电容的正极板和负极板上的电荷是相同的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:54.62,统计en,,0,0,0,,is the same for each capacitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:09:00.25,批注,,0,0,0,,类似并联电阻的公式
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:56.11,统计en,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you can factor out charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:09:00.25,统计ch,,0,0,0,,约掉Q以后 得到了串联电容的等效电容值
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.11,0:08:58.12,统计en,,0,0,0,,and you're left with the equation for equivalent capacitance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.12,0:09:00.25,统计en,,0,0,0,,of capacitors connected in series.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:01.82,统计en,,0,0,0,,So for series capacitors,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:05.79,统计ch,,0,0,0,,串联电容的等效电容值 小于所有单个电容的最小值
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:05.79,统计en,,0,0,0,,the combined capacitance is less than the weakest individual capacitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.79,0:09:07.08,统计en,,0,0,0,,And guess what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.79,0:09:07.08,统计ch,,0,0,0,,你猜怎么着
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.08,0:09:09.78,统计en,,0,0,0,,This wraps up our review of electricity!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.08,0:09:09.78,统计ch,,0,0,0,,电学我们就说到这了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.78,0:09:13.26,统计en,,0,0,0,,Now all that's left to learn about is the other side of this same force:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.78,0:09:13.26,统计ch,,0,0,0,,现在电磁力只剩下一半了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:14.97,统计en,,0,0,0,,the realm of magnetism!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:14.97,统计ch,,0,0,0,,也就是磁力！
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:16.83,统计en,,0,0,0,,Today we learned about Kirchhoff's Laws
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:16.83,统计ch,,0,0,0,,今天我们学习了基尔霍夫定律
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.83,0:09:19.39,统计en,,0,0,0,,and how we can rework conservation of charge and of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.83,0:09:19.39,统计ch,,0,0,0,,复习了电荷和能量守恒定理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.72,0:09:21.67,统计en,,0,0,0,,to analyze more complex  circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.72,0:09:21.67,统计ch,,0,0,0,,借以分析了更复杂的电路
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.98,0:09:25.60,统计en,,0,0,0,,We also discussed how capacitors function in a typical DC circuit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.98,0:09:25.60,统计ch,,0,0,0,,我们还讨论了电容在直流电路中的工作原理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.93,0:09:29.41,统计en,,0,0,0,,and the ways they behave when combined in series and parallel connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.93,0:09:29.41,统计ch,,0,0,0,,以及在串并联连接时的工作方式
